 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name scl2trd - Convert .scl disk images to .trd. @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}scl2trd@{"ub"} @{"i"}sclfile@{"ui"} "trdfile" 

@{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description scl2trd converts a .scl disk file to a 80 track, double sided (640Kb) .trd disk file. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Options @{"i"}sclfile@{"ui"} specifies a .scl file whose contents are to be converted. @{"i"}trdfile@{"ui"} specifies a .trd file to create. @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}Bugs None known. @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'fuse.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}fuse@{"ui"}(1) , @{" " link "'fuse-utils.1'/MAIN"}@{"i"}fuse-utils@{"ui"}(1) 

The comp.sys.sinclair Spectrum FAQ, at 
@{" " link "'http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html.guide/MAIN"}@{"i"}http://www.worldofspectrum.org/faq/index.html@{"ui"}. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Author Philip Kendall (philip-fuse@shadowmagic.org.uk). 

Dmitry Sanarins conversion routines from his Glukalka emulator are used. 


